						<div class="postbody">I'm new to the site and NES programming.  The basic architecture of the NES is making more sense each day, but I can't seem to wrap my head around pattern, name, and attribute tables, especially the extent to which they are interdependent.  
<br />
<br />The nestech docs, "How NES Graphics Work" file, and NES 101 tutorials all touch upon these concepts, but not clearly enough to make sense to me.  Anyone care to take a stab at these three in plain English?
<br />
<br />Thanks for helping a beginner.</div>

